                            <comment id="405257" author="JIRAUSER18021" created="Mon, 26 Feb 2024 15:01:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am closing this issue because the problem happens on unsupported kernels.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="394195" author="pjones" created="Fri, 24 Nov 2023 14:35:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Lustre 2.16 is targeting to support Ubuntu 22.04 clients. We really want to have cgroup support for Lustre and this is more complicated to do on older kernels but users wanting to use older kernels can use 2.15.x releases so this should not be an impediment to landing this code to master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="394193" author="JIRAUSER18021" created="Fri, 24 Nov 2023 13:56:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt;Does this problem only affect older unsupported kernels like Ubuntu 20.04?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=pjones&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;pjones&quot;&gt;pjones&lt;/a&gt; This happened on 20.04.5 (5.4.0-48-generic kernel). I haven&apos;t checked on any other versions. I have pushed &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/53220&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/53220&lt;/a&gt; to estimate whether something changed on other builds. BTW, what Ubuntu version should I use to test supported clients for master?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="394087" author="pjones" created="Thu, 23 Nov 2023 23:24:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Does this problem only affect older unsupported kernels like Ubuntu 20.04?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
